== Roasted Curried Parsnips ==

Preheat your #oven{} to 200°C. Remove the tops and bottoms from the @parsnips{4}(halved lengthways, no need to peel), then place on a #baking tray{}. Drizzle over some @oil{some}, the @mild curry powder{1%tbsp} and a pinch of @salt{pinch}. Mix with your hands, to ensure they get a good coating of oil and curry powder. Roast on the top shelf of your oven until cooked through and golden, about ~{30%minutes}.

== Cumin Bulgur Pilaf ==

Halve, peel and chop the @onion{1}(chopped into small pieces) into small pieces. Peel and grate the @garlic clove{1}(minced) (or use a #garlic press{}). Heat a drizzle of @oil{drizzle} in a large #saucepan{} on medium heat. Add the onion and cook until soft, ~{5%minutes}. Add the @bulgur wheat{100%g}, @ground cumin{2%tsp} and garlic.

> TIP: Add as much or as little cumin as you like!

Stir everything together and cook for ~{1%minute} before adding the @water{200%ml} and the @vegetable stock powder{1}. Bring to the boil and stir to dissolve the stock pot. Once boiling, place the @baby spinach{125%g} on top (don't stir it through), cover with a #lid{}, remove from the heat and leave to the side for ~{15%minutes} or until everything else is ready.

== Mint Yoghurt ==

While the parsnips and bulgur cook, roughly chop the @flat leaf parsley{1%bunch}(roughly chopped) and @mint{1}(roughly chopped, stalks and all). Put the @low fat natural yoghurt{150%g} in a #small bowl{}, add the mint and stir through.

== Pistachios ==

Remove the @pistachios{25%g} from their shells and pop in a #frying pan{} on medium-high heat (no oil). Cook until the pistachios are slightly toasted (but not burnt!), ~{3-4%minutes}. Remove them from the frying pan and keep to one side.

== To Serve ==

When the bulgur is ready, stir through the spinach. Season to taste with @salt{to taste} and @ground black pepper{to taste} if needed and add in the parsley. Serve the bulgur pilaf in #bowls{} with the curried parsnips on top and a spoonful of the minty yoghurt on the side. Sprinkle over the pistachios and @raisins{40%g}. Enjoy!